User Story – Enable Hardware Return Workflow per Counter

As a Le Comptoir Product Owner / administrator,
I want to enable or disable the Hardware Return workflow for a specific counter,
so that the pilot can be limited to selected counters without making the feature available globally.

Context

The Hardware Return workflow must be progressively deployed, starting with one or several pilot counters.

In the future, the activation will be managed through the Settings page using each counter’s VU Settings.
For this first pilot version, no front-end integration in the Settings page is required.

The objective of this story is only to implement the configuration/back-end capability so the workflow is available exclusively for enabled counters.

Functional Rules

* A new parameter must allow enabling or disabling the Hardware Return workflow for a counter.
* This parameter is defined at counter level within the VU Settings.
* By default, the workflow must be disabled for counters without configuration.
* If the parameter is enabled for a counter, the Hardware Return workflow actions must be available for this counter.
* If the parameter is disabled or missing, the workflow must not be accessible from this counter.
* For the pilot phase, the parameter can be updated directly in configuration/back-end without any administration UI.

Out of Scope

* No front-end integration in the Settings page.
* No visual toggle management in the administration interface.
* No modification of the existing Settings mockups already designed.
* No global deployment of the workflow to all counters.

Acceptance Criteria

AC1 – Counter-level activation parameter

Given an existing counter,
when a Hardware Return workflow activation parameter is defined in its VU Settings,
then the application can determine whether the workflow is enabled or disabled for this counter.

AC2 – Disabled by default

Given a counter without any configured parameter,
when the application checks the workflow activation status,
then the Hardware Return workflow is considered disabled.

AC3 – Workflow available for enabled counters

Given a counter for which the activation parameter is enabled,
when a coach accesses the available actions from this counter,
then the action allowing the launch of the Hardware Return workflow is available.

AC4 – Workflow hidden for non-enabled counters

Given a counter for which the activation parameter is disabled or missing,
when a coach accesses the available actions from this counter,
then the action allowing the launch of the Hardware Return workflow is not available.

AC5 – Pilot activation without Settings UI

Given the pilot phase context,
when the technical team needs to activate the workflow for a targeted counter,
then the activation can be performed directly through configuration/back-end without using a front-end Settings interface.
